1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual odometry and pose estimation using neural networks. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM), which is a crucial component in robotics. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses an end-to-end training approach to learn domain-specific features. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with developing a neural network solution for a real-world problem. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper uses a differentiable architecture and a novel graph optimization process.
